    "summary": "This section answers questions regarding the document's data visualization standards, specifically:\n- **What chart types are used?** Bar charts (柱状图) and line charts (折线图).\n- **What does each chart represent?** Bar charts display annual market revenue scale; line charts display annual market growth rate.\n- **What units are applied?** Revenue is measured in 100 million RMB (亿元/人民币); growth rate is measured in percentage (%).\n- **What is the temporal frequency?** Both metrics are tracked and presented on a yearly (每年) basis.\n- **How are market metrics visually differentiated?** Revenue data uses bar charts, while growth rate data uses line charts.\n\nCovers topics: data visualization conventions, market performance metrics. Entities: bar chart, line chart. Metrics: market revenue scale, market growth rate. Evidence type: quantitative visual data representation."
