    "summary": "**Topics:** Mobile game market revenue distribution by ranking tiers and multi-year trend analysis.\n**Dates:** 2023 (baseline data), 2025 (trend comparison), spanning a three-year observation period.\n**Metrics:** 2023 revenue shares: 1-10 rank (23.67%), 11-50 rank (26.82%), 51-200 rank (25.49%), Others (24.02%). 2025 shares: 11-50 rank (28.34%), 51-200 rank (25.37%). In-game displayed amount: 32,294,400.\n**Entities:** Five mobile games depicted in screenshots: a slot machine game, a flame-effect RPG, a MOBA game (UI text: “巅峰之巅少司命”), a pixel-style game, and a fantasy game (title: “特化世界：费”).\n**Claims/Trends:** Top 10 tier share fluctuated slightly over three years. Mid-tier (11-50) and lower-mid-tier (51-200) shares show upward trends from 2023 to 2025. \"Other\" games' share remains stable with a slight decline.\n**Figures/Tables:** A chart visualizing revenue share trends across ranking tiers, supplemented by five descriptive game screenshots positioned below it.\n**Evidence Types:** Quantitative market data (percentages), trend analysis statements, and visual evidence (data chart + annotated game screenshots).\n**Definitions/Procedures:** Not present in this section."
